model.pojo

Class LifeExpectancyEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.pojo.LifeExpectancyEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<LifeExpectancyEntry>, DataEntry, WorldData

    public class LifeExpectancyEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataEntry, WorldData, java.lang.Comparable<LifeExpectancyEntry>
    LifeExpectancyEntry is a POJO class that consumes all the data about a single Life Expectancy Survey for a country which is used by the rest of the program. A LifeExpectancyEntry Object encapsulates the state information needed to make markers of, this state information includes:
    • The country name that the entry is about
    • The country code that the entry is about
    • A Mapping between the years from 1960 to 2017 and their life expectancy value for the country

    Overrides the equals() , hashCode(), toString() methods

    12/7/2019
